      "span_text": "In conclusion, the results from the current study demonstrated that PTC contained more DE and ME and had a greater P digestibility than CC. The digestibility values of CP and AA in PTC were similar to those in CC. Therefore, if PTC is used to replace CC in pig diets, the DE and ME in the diet are likely to increase, less inorganic P will need to be supplemented to the diet, and fi nally, P excretion in the manure of pigs will be decreased."
